21:57.080 --> 21:58.877
- Hello!

22:01.080 --> 22:03.344
Bonjour!

22:03.390 --> 22:05.517
Mr. Jakov, isn't it?

22:05.550 --> 22:07.780
We met in Paris
a few months back.

22:07.820 --> 22:10.789
Sorry, I didn't mean
to startle you,

22:10.830 --> 22:13.355
it's just... here I was
and then, there you were...

22:13.400 --> 22:15.129
I never forget a face.

22:15.160 --> 22:18.368
- Antony Dimmond.
- Nice to be remembered.

22:18.400 --> 22:21.631
- You're hard to forget.
- What are you doing
in Florence?

22:21.670 --> 22:24.537
Are you working with Roman?
- Dr. Fell?

22:24.570 --> 22:27.004
- I heard he took an appointment
at the Capponi library.

22:27.040 --> 22:30.100
- Yes, he's the new curator
and translator at the
Palazzo CapponI.

22:30.140 --> 22:32.506
- Evidently, the last one
eloped with a woman

22:32.550 --> 22:35.110
or someone's
money or both.

22:35.150 --> 22:37.448
- That's the
commonly held belief.

22:37.490 --> 22:40.857
You just missed Roman.
- Did I?

22:40.890 --> 22:44.348
Was hoping
to take the piss.

22:46.690 --> 22:48.749
- Spare the piss for the time
being. If you're free,

22:48.800 --> 22:50.722
my wife and I would love
to have you for dinner.

23:31.870 --> 23:34.839
Listen.

23:34.880 --> 23:38.179
They prefer eating in company.

23:38.210 --> 23:41.976
I've kept cochlear gardens
since I was a young man,

23:42.020 --> 23:44.648
fattening snails
on herbs and vine leaves.

23:44.690 --> 23:46.885
Like all of us,
what they eat

23:46.920 --> 23:49.650
greatly influences and
enhances their flavor.

23:49.690 --> 23:52.181
- When I'm not busy
eating myself,

23:52.230 --> 23:55.893
you wish me to be
eating oysters,

23:55.930 --> 23:59.468
drinking sweet wines
and snacking on acorns.

23:59.500 --> 24:03.095
All to make me tastier?

24:03.140 --> 24:07.531
- Oh yes. And you are
making them tastier.

24:07.580 --> 24:10.140
- And I you.

24:10.180 --> 24:13.047
Imagine what you
must taste like.

24:13.080 --> 24:16.470
Won't be long until someone's
taking a bite out of you.

24:16.520 --> 24:19.580
- You're becoming
brighter, Abel.

24:19.620 --> 24:22.157
Dying hasn't dulled you one bit.

24:24.160 --> 24:28.654
- The snails are certainly
having a lovely experience,

24:28.700 --> 24:30.998
fattened on me

24:31.030 --> 24:33.567
in a red-wine marinade.

24:33.600 --> 24:35.966
They have no idea

24:36.000 --> 24:38.730
they're going to be eaten.

24:38.770 --> 24:42.570
We do.

24:42.610 --> 24:45.101
***

24:45.150 --> 24:49.940
(jazz music)

25:21.250 --> 25:23.309
- How well do you
know the Fells?

25:23.350 --> 25:27.719
- As well as anybody.
Which'd be not really.

25:27.760 --> 25:32.151
Lydia a friend of yours?

25:32.190 --> 25:34.249
- Not really.

25:34.300 --> 25:36.757
- I'd be surprised
to hear she had one.

25:36.800 --> 25:39.621
We share a mutual detestation.

25:39.670 --> 25:42.969
She disapproves
of my disapproval.

25:44.970 --> 25:46.631
- What do you disapprove of?

25:46.670 --> 25:49.833
- Roman, mainly. Lydia isn't
quite bright enough to see

25:49.880 --> 25:52.769
I'm just intimidated.
Roman does, of course.

25:52.810 --> 25:55.677
How he loves to strike fear.

25:55.720 --> 25:58.939
- Dante wrote that fear is
almost as bitter as death.

26:01.160 --> 26:04.687
- Dante wasn't dead
when he wrote it.

26:04.730 --> 26:08.154
- Are you traveling
alone, Antony?

26:08.200 --> 26:10.623
- The only way I travel.

26:10.670 --> 26:12.319
- Oh!

26:14.240 --> 26:17.767
Roman is speaking to the
Studiolo Friday, on Dante.

26:17.810 --> 26:21.132
You should come.
- Sounds appropriately hellish.

26:25.350 --> 26:28.069
Are you avoiding meats?

26:32.090 --> 26:35.059
- I'm trying not to eat anything
with a central nervous system.

26:35.090 --> 26:39.026
- Oysters, acorns and Marsala.

26:39.060 --> 26:40.891
