sophisticated palate.

26:57.310 --> 26:59.676
He's very particular

26:59.710 --> 27:02.838
about how I taste.

27:09.820 --> 27:11.629
- Is it that kind of party?

27:16.260 --> 27:19.889
- It's not that kind of party.

27:19.930 --> 27:22.330
- No,

27:22.370 --> 27:25.407
it really isn't.

27:25.440 --> 27:28.273
- Shame.

27:28.310 --> 27:30.437
You were both
suddenly so fascinating.

27:30.480 --> 27:33.040
Hm!

27:36.180 --> 27:39.013
- Buonasera.
- (both): Buonasera.

27:45.760 --> 27:48.126
- You let him go.

27:50.330 --> 27:52.298
- What would you
have me do, Bedelia?

28:27.870 --> 28:30.168
- Due bottiglie
di Btard-Montrachet

28:30.200 --> 28:31.963
e li tartufi bianchi,
per favore.

28:47.490 --> 28:49.458
- Grazie.

29:25.890 --> 29:28.996
(shalq breathing)

29:56.160 --> 29:59.129
(moan)

30:04.630 --> 30:06.860
- Bedelia.

30:09.270 --> 30:11.261
- He attacked me.

30:15.310 --> 30:18.245
- Is that your blood?

30:19.580 --> 30:22.174
- No.

30:29.460 --> 30:32.156
- You were defending yourself?

30:33.590 --> 30:37.048
- I was reckless.

30:39.530 --> 30:42.192
- This wasn't reckless violence.

30:42.240 --> 30:47.132
It was a controlled
use of force.

30:47.170 --> 30:50.276
- I know what happened.

30:50.310 --> 30:53.143
- Do you?

30:54.350 --> 30:56.944
- He was your patient
before he was mine.

31:01.020 --> 31:03.557
- He died under your care.

31:05.160 --> 31:07.628
You were not
defending yourself.

31:32.350 --> 31:34.386
- I can help you tell
the version of events

31:34.420 --> 31:36.854
you want to be told.

31:40.730 --> 31:43.324
I can help you...

31:43.360 --> 31:46.124
if you ask me to.

31:49.400 --> 31:51.209
- Will you help me?

32:05.390 --> 32:09.258
- In accord with my own taste
for the pre-Renaissance,

32:09.290 --> 32:12.589
I present the case
of Pietro della Vigna,

32:12.630 --> 32:17.090
whose treachery earned him
a place in Dante's Hell.

32:17.130 --> 32:19.690
- He was disgraced
and blinded for betraying

32:19.730 --> 32:23.291
his emperor's trust.

32:23.340 --> 32:25.661
Dante's pilgrim finds him
in the seventh level

32:25.710 --> 32:28.508
of the Inferno,
reserved for suicides.

32:28.540 --> 32:31.976
Like Judas Iscariot,
he died by hanging.

32:32.010 --> 32:36.014
Judas and Pietro della Vigna
are linked in Dante's Inferno.

32:36.050 --> 32:39.349
Betrayal, hanging...

32:39.390 --> 32:42.279
then, linked
since antiquity,

32:42.320 --> 32:44.424
the image appearing
again and again in art.

32:44.460 --> 32:48.248
This is the earliest
known depiction

32:48.300 --> 32:51.599
of the Crucifixion, carved
on an ivory box in Gaul

32:51.630 --> 32:55.430
about A.D. four hundred. It
includes the death by hanging

32:55.470 --> 33:00.760
of Judas, his face upturned to
the branch that suspends him.

33:00.810 --> 33:02.573
On the doors of
the Benevento Cathedral,

33:02.610 --> 33:05.204
