with his bowels falling out.

33:05.250 --> 33:09.038
And here, from a
fifteenth-century edition

33:09.080 --> 33:11.719
of The Inferno, is
Pietro della Vigna's body

33:11.750 --> 33:14.685
hanging from a bleeding tree.

33:14.720 --> 33:17.587
I won't belabor the parallels
with Judas Iscariot.

33:17.620 --> 33:20.350
Betrayal, hanging,
self-destruction.

33:20.390 --> 33:24.065
"Io fei gibetto a me
de le mie case."

33:26.600 --> 33:30.092
"I make my own home
be my gallows."

33:30.140 --> 33:34.236
- Mr. Dimmond. Welcome.
